&amp;lt;h2&amp;gt;Classification&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;6000 English and 6000 French user reviews from three applications on Google Play (Garmin Connect, Huawei Health, Samsung Health) are labelled manually. We employed three labels: problem report, feature request, and irrelevant.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;ul&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Problem reports&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; show the issues the users have experienced while using the app.&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Feature requests&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp;reflect the demande of users on new function, new content, new interface, etc.&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Irrelevant&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; are the user reviews that do not belongs to the two aforementioned categories.&amp;lt;/li&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/ul&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;As we can observe from the following table, that shows examples of labelled user reviews, each review belongs to one or more categories.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;
